  "name": "MeanReversion_BB_KVO_Trader",
  "description": "This algorithm implements a mean-reverting strategy using Bollinger Bands and the Klinger Volume Oscillator. It identifies entry points for long positions when the price closes below the lower Bollinger Band, indicating potential oversold conditions, combined with low volatility as indicated by the Bollinger Bands Width.",
  "algorithm_type": "MeanReverting",
  "prompt": "Create an expert-level Mean Reverting trading algorithm in Python that operates on 15-minute bars. Use a combination of the Bollinger Bands Width indicator and the Klinger Volume Oscillator to identify entry points: enter long when price closes below the lower Bollinger Band, the Bollinger Bands Width is below its 20-period moving average (indicating low volatility), and the Klinger Volume Oscillator crosses above zero, signaling volume-driven reversal. Exit the long position when price closes above the middle Bollinger Band or when the Klinger Volume Oscillator turns negative. Use a 20-period simple moving average for Bollinger Bands and 34, 55 periods for Klinger parameters. Implement a stop loss at 1.5% below entry and a take profit at 3% above entry. Include position sizing based on average true range over 14 periods to adjust risk per trade.",
